HEADWORD: Hesitation
<hw>Hes`i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>haesitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧sitation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of hesitating; suspension of opinion or action;
doubt; vacillation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A faltering in speech; stammering.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hesitative</ent>⟦br⟧
